<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">PEANUT BUTTER BROWNIE CUPS</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page054.article001.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY MARCY BLACK SIMPSON</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 1½ dozen cups or brownies </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 (19.9-ounce) box brownie mix </p><p class="no-indent">18 miniature peanut butter cup candies, unwrapped </p><p class="no-indent">1 (10-ounce) bag peanut butter morsels </p><p class="no-indent">3 tablespoons heavy whipping cream </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare brownie batter according to package directions. Line 18 muffin cups with paper liners. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. Spoon 1 tablespoon brownie batter into each muffin cup. Place 1 peanut butter cup into each muffin cup. Top with remaining brownie batter. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until center is set. Let cool on wire racks. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. In a medium saucepan, combine peanut butter morsels and cream. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring often, until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Spread evenly over brownie cupcakes.</p></div>
